response.value:
The issue is likely caused by this CSS rule:
```css
section {
  display: none;
  padding: 1rem;
}
```
This hides all `<section>` elements by default, including your sidebar and content area (which contains the listings). However, you have custom classes (`sidebar`, `content-area`, `active`) that should override this, but if those classes do not explicitly set `display: flex` or `block`, the sections will remain hidden.

To fix this, I will update your CSS so that `.sidebar` and `.content-area` are always visible and use the correct display property.

